`BufferedReader` will continue reading from `InputStream` as long as the stream is open.

Your code will stay stuck until `InputStream` gets closed by the data source you are reading from, or until you close it yourself from a different `Thread` in your application by calling `cmdin.close()`.

If you simply wanna read whatever is available on the `InputStream` at the moment, you can do something along the lines of:
```
var buffer = new byte[cmdsin.available()];
cmdsin.read(buffer);
cmdsin.close();

var lines = new String(buffer, StandardCharsets.UTF_8).lines();
lines.forEach(line -&gt; System.out.println(&quot;CMD: &quot; + line));
```
Note that `String#lines` is only availble from Java 11.

